From:    Douglas Rudd <rudd@plk.af.mil>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


> a banner tacked to a wall with the center sagging down.  i have tried a box
> object, subdivide multiple times, and then deform but its not quite right.
> any other ideas?
> 
I havn't actually tried this, but it seems than a good gray scale bit map of
your banner "Appliqued" to a high point count plane may do the trick. It 
would take a lot of ram and slow things down a bit. You might also try a clip
and altitude map set on a simple plane. I agree that clip maps take a little 
more work, but anyone who has seen what Snap Maps can do should agree it's
worth the effort.


