@node IML-123 " MSG-123  Subject: Amazing et al
@toc contents

Subject: Amazing et al
Date:    Saturday, 08 October 1994 00:18:18 
From:    KEN_ROBERTSON@robelle.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


I think that Impulse's attitude may be that of "if it ain't
broke, don't fix it".

I would guess that they get pretty excited about writing new advancements
in the rendering/object design engines, and don't have the time to
implement those two features.

Some possible reasons that the ASL requestor has not been implemented:
   1.  See the main reason above.
   2.  The ASL requestors require certain data structures, their own
       requestors may have COMPLETELY different data structures that
       Imagine, at a low-level, is dependant upon.  (This may not be
       the best design!)
   3.  Impulse would prefer that the requestors look the same, no matter
       the platform Imagine is running on.

Just a thot.

PS:  I tried the global lens flare that came with 3.1, and although the
default settings looked kind of neat, I sure wouldn't use the FX for stills.
The halos sure look great in HAM-8!  Excellent shading, Impulse!

\KenR
