Subject: Re: Brush Maps
Date:    Sunday, 09 October 1994 01:19:38 
From:    williamp@triode.apana.org.au


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


> I have a brush map that I want to place on an object (like a decal.)  Is
> there a way to make some areas of the brush transparent?  I've tried many
> different methods, making the transparent areas black or white, layering a
> transparency map over the decal, etc. but no luck.  Is there some way to do
> this that I've overlooked?

Use the genlock button on the brush requester with the image you want to 
decal having colour 0 as the transparent area.Don't use 24bit IFFs.

DPaint works well at creating the decal images.



