@node IML-136 " MSG-136  Subject: Re: Amazing et al
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Amazing et al
Date:    Sunday, 09 October 1994 08:37:59 
From:    mrivers@tbag.tscs.com (Michael Rivers)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


[reasons why ASL file reqs aren't in Imagine]
TH> I guess they didn't look too good with the rest of the GUI having a
TH> totally different style. Maybe it's time to go style guide compliant?

If Impulse had, at the very minimum, opened the screen with the
WB2 3-D look, the ASL would have looked fine. But Imagine opens
a screen that uses the Amiga's monochrome windowing system which
is why the editors window borders and requester's like the Memory
and 'Overwrite existing file' requesters are just black and grey
and why the ASL 'looked like hell'. IMO ASL(monochrome or not) is
still better than Imagines file req.

(BTW I've written my own system hack which makes Imagine open the screen
with the WB2 3-D look and the windows and requesters look *MUCH* better)
