Subject: IMAGINE 3.0
Date:    Monday, 10 October 1994 09:55:37 
From:    cjo <cjo@smtpgw.esrange.ssc.se>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


Sara Zdenek wrote;
>I have AMIGA 1200 with 2 megs.  Can I run Imagine 3.0 on this
>configuration  (without coprocesor) ???

Sure you can run it.
But you won't be able to do any complicated stuff with only 2 megs.
I have seen somewhere that 6 megs are a minimum and 9 megs are recommended
in order to use the program properly.

As for the FPU; well, it helps. It makes rendering a lot faster, but it is
not necessary for the program to run.

I think a Blizzard-accelerator would help you (1220 or 1230).

