        Except *me*, I guess.  'Course I only signed up in August,
        and this is still '94, so what the heck.

        I recently posted a mini-tip I discovered when trying to
        place a bunch o' copies of an object in a circle.  It didn't
        make it to the list for some reason, so here it is again.  I
        thought it was kinda cool--not cool enough to see twice, so
        I hope the errant post doesn't show up too...

        Anyway, place the first object, and then add an axis where
        the center of the circle would be.  Copy/Paste the obj, then
        pick first the axis then the obj.  Now Rotate to the desired
        degree reading, eg 60, if you're placing 6 objects.  The axis
        makes it work just like drawing with a compass.

        -mikeT


