On Oct 19,  4:50pm, David Nagy wrote:
> I use Steve's 'Forge' program and love it.  Has anyone wrote a config 
> file for Forge that allows it to 'understand' the new Imagine3.0 
> textures?  What I mean is: Forge knows what the 'default' settings are 
> and for all the Essense textures. (Along with info on how to set up the 
> sliders)  Is there a file that allows Forge to easily manipulate 
> Impulse's latest textures?

I'm pretty sure it's more than a config file issue here.  Essence textures are
compiled with extre information in them so that they can be used correctly 
with Forge.  When I bought Forge, I had to get the latest version of the
Essence textures in order to use them with the program.  What would be nice
if Impulse or Apex would write a patch for all of the Imagine Textures that
would add on the extra info that Forge needs.  Has Apex publically released
the format that Forge reads?

Cedric
