When adding an object you don't get a DOF requestor - you
_do_ get a layer requestor, however.
The manual says "Use the hide layers function in the stage editor".
This functionality supposedly helps when your scenes are too
clutterred, I guess.

I _was_ playing around with Depth-Of-Field this week-end.
I like the quickrenders' easy ability to set the distance -
why didn't they do it in a similar fashion for the action
editor - camera dof requestor?
