@node IML-335 " MSG-335  Subject: Banging Your Head on A Wall...
@toc contents

Subject: Banging Your Head on A Wall...
Date:    Thursday, 27 October 1994 22:05:47 
From:    KEN_ROBERTSON@robelle.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


Joe@Ensoniq wrote:
>I've banged my head against a wall long enough, I need some help.  I create
>a chrome ball, (chrome attrs plus metals texture).  When I place the object
>in my scene and ray-trace it everything works OK (i.e,. properly reflects
>its environment).  When I try to place the ball inside of a glass tube, it
>no longer reflects anything!!.

I tried this out with Imagine 3.1 and...as long as the reflection of the
glass tube is at 1.00, the sphere reflects properly.

However, bump it up to 1.01, and poof!  The reflections on the sphere
disappear.

I called up Imagine Tech Support to find out why.  The techie, (very
friendly too!) said that "Ooh, combining reflections and refractions,
that's a tough one to do."  It boils down to, Imagine 3.1 cannot do
this function.  Sorry.

I can't think of any work-arounds off-hand, either.

\KenR
