@node IML-357 " MSG-357  Subject: Photo-Realistic Xmas Trees
@toc contents

Subject: Photo-Realistic Xmas Trees
Date:    Friday, 28 October 1994 18:53:59 
From:    KEN_ROBERTSON@robelle.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  


Does this have to be animatable?  Are you going to zoom around the tree?
I've used trees as backdrops quite successfully by pasting a 2-plane
bit-map (a 2-d sketch) onto planes.  The scene was an outdoors, snow-
covered one.  Looked pretty good, as long as you didn't get too close.

If you were going to pan, here's an idea.  Get a digitized photo of the
tree, and past it on concentric ars (sort of like contentric circles,
but they don't go all of the way around.)  I.e.
                      (
                     (  (
                    (  (  (
                     (  (
                      (

Make the arcs semi-transparent, and use genlock when you past the
bit-maps.

Perhaps use 5 or 6 arcs.  As you pan, you will see movement.
As long as there is no close-up stuff, this may pass.
\KenR


